						<summary>

						<p>Stones are out of order. Below this is an incomplete inscription and disjointed pieces. It records the gift of land after purchase for providing food offering to the god Ugarayāṇḍār by Siṟiyāṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śivaṉukkiniyāṉ and Āṇḍāṉ Ālālas[undaraṉ] by depositing 24 coins at temple treasury.</p>						

						</summary>
